;;
    replay) cat <<'EOF'
skytest replay <mod> <script.steps> — boot a test session, run a .steps script to snap the
world to a target state (console staging + real input, probe-gated), then leave it DETACHED
and live for probing. The session stays up on success AND on a step failure (then: skytest stop).
  <mod>        a Data-shaped folder or a single .dll/.esp/.esl/.esm (resolved like `test`)
  <script>     bare name -> mods/<mod-dir>/<name>.steps; a path (has '/') as-is; '-' = stdin
  --with a,b   extra framework DLLs (prefix match), like `test`
  --headless   no window (offscreen render); default is a window nested in Hyprland
  --dry-run    print the normalized step plan and exit (a lint; no boot, no profile change)
.steps verbs: exec <console> | tap <key> | key <k…> | hold <LMB|RMB|key> <dur|until:C> |
              wait <dur|until:C> | shot [name].   Gates: until:inworld, until:menu:<Name>.
