;;
    drive) cat <<'EOF'
skytest drive <cmd> … — inject input into the test session via libei (isolated to it).
  tap <key>            press+release one key            (e.g. drive tap enter)
  seq <key> …          tap several keys in order        (e.g. drive seq down down enter)
  key <key> <0|1>      hold(1)/release(0) one key
  click [<x> <y>]      click at (x,y), or at current cursor if omitted
  abs <x> <y>          move cursor to pixel (x,y)
  rel <dx> <dy>        relative pointer move (1 unit = 1 px)
  raw <eidriver args>  pass through verbatim
Keys: esc enter tab space backspace up down left right pageup pagedown home end
      tilde/console e r m w a s d f y n j i
Examples:
  skytest drive seq down down enter
  skytest drive click 1195 556
EOF
;;
    stop) cat <<'EOF'
skytest stop — tear down the running gamescope test session and restore Data → full
(+ Plugins.txt). Kills by gamescope session, so a real game in the same prefix is safe.
Examples:
  skytest stop
EOF
;;
    play) cat <<'EOF'
skytest play — launch the full modded game over the fast direct SKSE path
Examples:
  skytest play
EOF
;;
    playtest) cat <<'EOF'
skytest playtest — launch the FULL modded profile under a DRIVABLE gamescope session
(real load order + SkyUI + every SKSE plugin), so MCMs and load-order-dependent mods can be
screenshot/driven — the vanilla+1 `test` profile can't reach those. No SkytestProbe in 'full',
so ready/exec don't apply: use shot/drive and read the in-game console / SKSE logs. Boots to the
menu; load a save via drive. Tear down with skytest stop.
  --headless   no window (offscreen render); default is a window nested in Hyprland
  --sdl        visible fallback if wayland misbehaves under Hyprland
Examples:
  skytest playtest
  skytest playtest --headless
EOF
;;
    normal) cat <<'EOF'
skytest normal — force Data → full (recover after an interrupted test or crash)
Examples:
  skytest normal
EOF
;;
    uninstall) cat <<'EOF'
skytest uninstall — revert Data to the original real directory, remove profiles
Examples:
